    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of April 4 article about prospects of adding statue of Mark McGwire to those honoring great St Louis Cardinals players, one of whom was misnamed</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A sports article last Wednesday about the prospect of adding a statue of Mark McGwire to those honoring great St. Louis Cardinals players gave an incorrect given name in some copies for a catcher for the old St. Louis Browns whom the creator of the statues, Harry Weber, considered a baseball hero. He was Clint Courtney, not Cliff.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A sports article last Wednesday about the prospect of adding a statue of Mark McGwire to those honoring great St. Louis Cardinals players gave an incorrect given name in some copies for a catcher for the old St. Louis Browns whom the creator of the statues, Harry Weber, considered a baseball hero. He was Clint Courtney, not Cliff.</p>
      </block>
